<hr WIDTH="100%">
<center><b><font color="#CC0000">"Terence Green's science fiction is quintessentially
Canadian, with its graceful focus on characterization, its rhetorical understatement,
its placing of characters in a complex social environment, as well as its
refusal to explore techhnology for its own sake alone."</font></b>
<br><b><font color="#009900"><i>- </i>Douglas Barbour <i>(Professor Emeritus
of English, University of Alberta)</i></font></b>
<br><b><font color="#009900">St. James Guide to Science Fiction Writers</font></b></center>

