<td VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="75%"><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b>Charles
de Lint in The Ottawa Citizen</b>: "its thematic thrust is universal...
invigorating and convincing."</font></font>
<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b>Quill &amp; Quire</b>:
"a compelling novel... enjoyable and stimulating."</font></font>
<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b>Canadian Book Review Annual</b>:
"a glorious mix of time, space, and philosophies."</font></font>
<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b>The Edmonton Journal</b>:
"dramatic and exciting... never quite stops to catch its breath."</font></font>
<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b>Fredericton Daily</b>:
"I was left breathless... beautiful and powerful."</font></font>
<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b><a href="rbwbic.html">Books
in Canada</a></b>: "gracefully and authoritatively written... the book
touches brilliance."</font></font>
<br>&nbsp;
<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b><i>Children of the Rainbow</i></b>
is out of print. Autographed Copies are available, though, by contacting
the author via E-Mail (above).&nbsp;</font></font>
<br>&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
</table>

<p>
