<p>
<hr SIZE=1 WIDTH="90%">
<table BORDER=0 WIDTH="100%" >
<tr>
<td><a NAME="wind"></a><b><font face="Comic Sans MS"><font size=+1>The
Woman Who is</font></font></b>
<br><b><font face="Comic Sans MS"><font size=+1>&nbsp;&nbsp; the Midnight
Wind</font></font></b>
<br><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1>(Pottersfield Press, Canada,
1987)</font></font></td>

<td>
<center><b><font color="#000000"><font size=-1>Collects the stories</font></font></b>
<br><b><i><font color="#CC0000"><font size=-1>Ashland, Kentucky, Barking
Dogs, Legacy, The Woman Who is the Midnight Wind,&nbsp;</font></font></i></b>
<br><b><i><font color="#CC0000"><font size=-1>Room 1786, Japanese Tea,
SusieQ2,</font></font></i></b>
<br><b><i><font color="#CC0000"><font size=-1>Till Death Do Us Part, Point
Zero, Of Children in the Foliage</font></font></i></b></center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>
<center><img SRC="midwdcv.jpg" ALT="The Woman Who is the Midnight Wind" HSPACE=20 height=226 width=144></center>
</td>

<td><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b><a href="mwottcit.html">The
Ottawa Citizen</a></b>: "an inspiring read... It reaches out to touch your
heart, mind and soul. Highly recommended."</font></font>
<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b><a href="http://www.hatrack.com/osc/reviews/f&sf/88-05.html">Orson
Scott Card in The Magazine of Fantasy &amp; Science Fiction</a></b>: "Terence
Green's first collection is a milestone for all of us."</font></font>
<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b>Canadian Literature</b>:
"ingenious and intelligent fantasies... his ultimate subjects are the imponderables
of human morality."</font></font>
<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b>SF Chronicle</b>: "masterful
understatement... extraordinary... indicates a great talent."</font></font>
<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><a href="http://www.sfsite.com/vault/bksg02.htm"><b>SF
Site</b>:</a> "one of the best collections of the eighties."</font></font>
<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b><a href="http://www.collectionscanada.ca/3/6/t6-205-e.html">The
National Library of Canada</a></b>: "shifts of time, futuristic technology
and alien cultures open the door for Terence Green's specialty -- the study
of relationships, particularly those between parents and children."</font></font>
<p><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=-1><b>Books in Canada</b>: "(Green's)
new collection of short stories is simply good fiction."</font></font>
<br>&nbsp;
<br>&nbsp;
<p>&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
</table>

